                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 5.  <span>Apoptosis pathway with genes displaying increased expression (colored red) and decreased expression in carcinoma-like samples (colored green).</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec4.fig2.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec4.fig2.caption1.p1"></a><p>Carcinoma-like samples had higher expression of pro-apoptotic genes such as BAX, BID, CASP8, and AIF. These samples also expressed higher levels of anti-apoptotic factors such as IKK, Bcl-xl, and c-IAP2. Adenoma-like samples had higher Bcl-2 expression than carcinoma-like samples.</p>
